description:
Winter is here and while many around the country have packed their garden tools away, we are taking them out. In Central Florida, this is an ideal time to have a garden as the temperature is cool and the bugs are less active. However, for first-time gardeners, having a garden is a wonderful idea but maintenance may be a challenge. A few careful steps executed now will make your efforts worthwhile.
Things to consider to have a successful garden involves:
1. Removing dead leaves and diseased plants as they may infect other plants or attract pests and funguses. 
2. Deep watering is far better than sprinkling for several minutes a day.
3. Practice succession planting to ensure a consistent harvest. 
4. Weed often to prevent overcrowding and depletion on nutrients. 
For those not able to have a garden because of harsh winter conditions, fall is a good time to add soil amendments like compost, green manure, or organic fertilizers to the spring beds. This will allow time for them to start breaking down and enriching your soil in preparation for spring planting. 
Here is a link to a more in-depth tree planting video .Seed Time and Harvest: God's Way to Plant a Fruit Tree). God's way to plant a fruit tree.
